This paper deals with medical image segmentation, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves modifying a neural network architecture, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of brain symmetry as a feature also suggests a potential application of neural networks in neuroscience (cs.NE). Finally, the paper involves natural language processing in the form of text classification (cs.CL), which is a minor aspect of the work but still relevant.
